Use Case Document
Product: LOGOS – Cognitive Engine + Stakeholder Engagement MVP
________________________________________
1. Introduction
1.1 Purpose
This document describes the primary use cases for:
•	LOGOS Core (the cognitive engine and shared AI pipelines), and
•	The Stakeholder Engagement MVP that runs on LOGOS Core.
It focuses on user-visible behaviour and interactions with the system; technical design details are covered in the SRS, AI Model Design, and SAD.
1.2 Scope
Use cases in scope:
•	Ingesting and processing stakeholder interactions (documents, audio, notes).
•	Reviewing and committing extracted data into the LOGOS graph.
•	Searching and exploring stakeholders, projects, and commitments.
•	Managing commitments and viewing alerts.
•	Viewing project maps and stakeholder networks.
•	Basic configuration and operations relevant to MVP.
Advanced modules (ESG analytics, governance workflows, predictive modelling, etc.) are out of scope for this version but should be supported by the same patterns.
________________________________________
2. Actors
Actor	Description
Business User	Category Manager, Project Lead, Analyst. Regularly ingests interactions, manages commitments.
Executive Viewer	Senior manager/executive. Mainly views dashboards, stakeholder profiles, and alerts.
System Administrator	Technical user. Installs, configures, and maintains LOGOS and Neo4j.
Data/AI Engineer	Extends pipelines, tunes models, maintains knowledgebase/prompts and domain profiles.
LOGOS Core (System)	Internal system actor representing pipelines, graph store, and reasoning engine.
Local AI Services	External system actors: local LLM, ASR, OCR (optional, via HTTP).
For most use cases, the Primary Actor is the Business User.
________________________________________
3. Use Case List
UC01 – Ingest Stakeholder Interaction from Document
UC02 – Ingest Stakeholder Interaction from Audio
UC03 – Ingest Stakeholder Interaction via Free-text Note
UC04 – Review and Confirm Extracted Data (Preview & Commit)
